<h1>Buffalo Corporate Attorney</h1>

<p>VMG Business Advisory, PLLC is a Buffalo-based corporate and business law firm serving founders, startups, investors, and established companies throughout Western New York and nationwide.</p>

<p>Connor T. Godfrey, founder and principal attorney, earned his J.D. from the University at Buffalo School of Law and trained at two of Buffalo's leading corporate law firms — <strong>Harter Secrest &amp; Emery LLP</strong> and <strong>Lippes Mathias LLP</strong> — before founding VMG Business Advisory, PLLC. He also brings a finance background from his work as a financial analyst in portfolio management and banking, which allows him to provide legal advice grounded in real business and financial judgment alongside the legal analysis.</p>

<h2>Corporate and Business Legal Services in Buffalo</h2>

<p>VMG Business Advisory provides targeted legal services across the full range of corporate and transactional matters that Buffalo businesses face:</p>

<ul>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/corporate-governance/" style="color: #001f3f;">Corporate Governance</a> — board structure, fiduciary duties, governance policies, and internal controls</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/mergers-acquisitions/" style="color: #001f3f;">Mergers &amp; Acquisitions</a> — business purchases and sales, asset transactions, and joint ventures</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/startup-advisory/" style="color: #001f3f;">Startup Advisory</a> — entity formation, founder agreements, IP protection, and early-stage legal counsel</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/venture-capital-safe-negotiation/" style="color: #001f3f;">Venture Capital &amp; Startup Financing</a> — SAFE agreements, convertible notes, and priced equity rounds</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/private-placements-securities/" style="color: #001f3f;">Private Offerings &amp; Securities</a> — Regulation D compliance, SAFE instruments, and private capital raises</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/outside-general-counsel/" style="color: #001f3f;">Outside General Counsel</a> — ongoing legal support for businesses without full-time in-house counsel</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/professional-service-entities/" style="color: #001f3f;">Licensed Professional Firms</a> — PC, PLLC, and LLP formation and transactions for regulated professionals</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/not-for-profit/" style="color: #001f3f;">Nonprofit Organizations</a> — 501(c) formation, governance, and compliance</li>
  <li><a href="/practice-areas/business-financial-advisory/" style="color: #001f3f;">Business &amp; Financial Advisory</a> — financial modeling, business viability analysis, and strategic advisory</li>
</ul>

<h2>Serving Buffalo and Western New York</h2>

<p>Buffalo's business community spans established manufacturers, healthcare organizations, professional service firms, and a growing technology and startup sector. VMG Business Advisory serves clients across all of these industries — from early-stage founders forming their first entity to mature companies navigating acquisitions, governance matters, or complex transactions.</p>

<p>Working with a local attorney who trained in Buffalo, understands the Western New York business environment, and is familiar with New York's specific legal requirements offers a practical advantage for businesses operating in the region. At the same time, VMG Business Advisory serves clients nationwide — particularly in venture capital, startup advisory, and SMR nuclear energy — so clients with multi-state or national operations are equally well-served.</p>

<h2>Why Work With VMG Business Advisory</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Local foundation:</strong> Connor earned his law degree at UB School of Law and began his career at Harter Secrest &amp; Emery and Lippes Mathias — two of Buffalo's preeminent corporate law firms</li>
